# World Mini App (MiniKit)

## Overview

`apps/web` is configured as a World Mini App — a web app that runs inside the World App webview via the MiniKit SDK. MiniKit is initialized by wrapping the app with `MiniKitProvider` in the root layout.

## Packages

- `@worldcoin/minikit-js` — core SDK (commands, provider, types, verification helpers)
- `@worldcoin/minikit-react` — React hooks (`useWaitForTransactionReceipt`, etc.)

## Environment Variables

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORLD_APP_ID` — your App ID from the [Developer Portal](https://developer.worldcoin.org/) (format: `app_xxxxxxxxxx`)
- `WORLD_APP_DEV_PORTAL_API_KEY` — server-side API key for verify/payment confirmation (never expose to the client)

## Provider Setup

`MiniKitProvider` wraps the app inside `<body>` in `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx`. The wrapper component lives at `@/components/minikit-provider`. Do not remove or reorder it.

## Commands

All MiniKit commands are dispatched from client components. Use the **async pattern** (`MiniKit.commandsAsync.*`) as the default — it returns a promise with `finalPayload`. The event-listener pattern (`MiniKit.subscribe`) is available but less common.

Available commands: `verify`, `pay`, `walletAuth`, `sendTransaction`, `signMessage`, `shareContacts`, `requestPermission`, `getPermissions`, `sendHapticFeedback`, `share`, `chat`.

### Guard with `isInstalled()`

Always check `MiniKit.isInstalled()` before dispatching any command. This returns `true` only when the app is running inside World App.

```typescript
if (!MiniKit.isInstalled()) {
  return;
}
const { finalPayload } = await MiniKit.commandsAsync.verify(payload);
```

## Backend Verification

**All proof and payment verification MUST happen server-side.** Users can manipulate the frontend. API routes live under `src/app/api/minikit/`:

- `verify/route.ts` — verifies World ID proofs via `verifyCloudProof()`
- `confirm-payment/route.ts` — confirms payments via Developer Portal API
- `nonce/route.ts` — generates SIWE nonce for wallet auth
- `complete-siwe/route.ts` — verifies SIWE signatures via `verifySiweMessage()`

## Authentication

Use **Wallet Auth** (SIWE) as the primary auth flow — not the Verify command. The flow:

1. Frontend fetches a nonce from `/api/minikit/nonce`
2. Frontend calls `MiniKit.commandsAsync.walletAuth({ nonce, ... })`
3. Frontend posts the signed payload + nonce to `/api/minikit/complete-siwe`
4. Backend verifies the SIWE message and creates a session

## User Identity

- Always display `MiniKit.user.username` — never show raw wallet addresses
- Access profile picture via `MiniKit.user.profilePictureUrl`
- Check `MiniKit.user.optedIntoOptionalAnalytics` before collecting analytics; if `false`, do not track

## Convenience Hook

`@/hooks/use-minikit` exports `useMiniKit()` providing `isInstalled`, `user`, `deviceProperties`, and `launchLocation`.

## Design Rules (Webview Constraints)

- **Padding:** default 24px around content
- **No `alert()` / `confirm()` / `prompt()`** — alert dialogs are disabled on iOS webview
- **Use `100dvh`** instead of `100vh` to account for dynamic viewport
- **Set `overscroll-behavior: none`** on `html, body` to prevent iOS bounce
- **No footers, sidebars, or hamburger menus** — use bottom tab navigation and anchored buttons
- **Target load time:** 2-3 seconds max for initial load, under 1 second for subsequent actions
- **No zooming:** viewport already sets `user-scalable=false`

## Safe Area Insets

The root layout includes `viewport-fit=cover`. Use CSS `env(safe-area-inset-*)` for fixed-position elements. Device insets are also available at `MiniKit.deviceProperties.safeAreaInsets`.

## Haptic Feedback

Use `MiniKit.commands.sendHapticFeedback()` on important interactions:

- `impact` (light/medium/heavy) — for UI element collisions
- `notification` (success/warning/error) — for action outcomes
- `selectionChanged` — for checkbox/toggle state changes

## Payments

- Supported tokens: WLD, USDC on World Chain
- Minimum transfer: $0.1
- Whitelist recipient addresses in the Developer Portal
- Always verify payments server-side via the Developer Portal API
- Use `tokenToDecimals()` helper for amount formatting

## Transactions

- Whitelist contracts in Developer Portal (Configuration → Advanced)
- Users get 500 free transactions/day; 1M gas limit per transaction
- Approvals are not supported — use Permit2 for token spending
- Use `useWaitForTransactionReceipt` from `@worldcoin/minikit-react` to poll for confirmation

## Notifications

1. Request permission: `MiniKit.commandsAsync.requestPermission({ permission: Permission.Notifications })`
2. Enable notifications in Developer Portal Advanced settings
3. Send via Developer Portal API or the send-notification endpoint (server-side)
4. Support localized notifications for better engagement

## Quick Actions (Deep Links)

Link to your mini app: `https://world.org/mini-app?app_id={app_id}&path={path}`

The `path` parameter should be URL-encoded and maps to your Next.js app routes.

## Sharing

- Use `MiniKit.commandsAsync.share()` for native OS share sheet
- Use `MiniKit.commandsAsync.shareContacts()` to access user contacts (returns `username` + `walletAddress`)

## Localization

World App users span many regions. Prioritize: Portuguese, Korean, Japanese, Thai, Spanish, English. The existing i18n setup with i18next handles this — add translation keys for all MiniKit-related UI strings.

## Testing

- Use your App ID at the [testing page](https://docs.world.org/mini-apps/quick-start/testing) and scan the QR code with World App
- Use [Eruda](https://github.com/liriliri/eruda) for mobile console logs
- Use ngrok/zrok for local testing with World App
- Use the [L2 Faucet](https://www.l2faucet.com/world) for testnet WLD on Sepolia

## Do NOT

- Hardcode app IDs — use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_WORLD_APP_ID`
- Verify proofs or payments on the frontend — always use server-side API routes
- Use `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()` — they are disabled in iOS webview
- Show wallet addresses to users — always show usernames
- Use the Verify command for login — use Wallet Auth (SIWE) instead
- Use `100vh` — use `100dvh` for full-height layouts
- Skip the `MiniKit.isInstalled()` guard before any command
- Collect analytics when `MiniKit.user.optedIntoOptionalAnalytics` is `false`
